      "narrative": "***There are 12 pigeons and three macaws housed in three round enclosures connected by suspended walkways. There\nare nest box/shelters provided in each of the enclosures but may not be of sufficient number to accommodate the number\nof birds in the enclosure. The enclosure provides a pitched roof that will protect them from the rain but protection from the\ncold is limited. Additional shelters shall be provided to allow for all birds present in the enclosure to be able to access\nshelter from the wind and cold.\nCorrect by November 28, 2025.\nThis inspection and exit interview were conducted with the Manager.\nn"
